    "actions_taken": [
      "Pipe fitter self-rescued by swimming to platform boat landing",
      "Incident reported to QCP supervisor, TCR, and HSE",
      "BSEE conducted on-site incident follow-up on August 9, 2021",
      "Talos Field Foreman initiated investigation"
    ],
    "summary": "On August 7, 2021, at approximately 3:00 pm, a Quality Construction and Production Pipe Fitter fell through pre-cut corroded grating on the plus 10 deck into the Gulf of Mexico at Vermilion Block 331 on Talos Energy platform A while replacing corroded grating. The pipe fitter was able to self-rescue by swimming to the platform's boat landing. The incident was not immediately reported to the Person in-Charge, and no man overboard alarms were sounded nor ring buoy deployed.",
    "recommendations": [
      "BSEE Lake Charles District recommends that Office of Incident Investigations and Office of Safety Management together draft a safety alert to prevent a reoccurrence of the incident with findings in report"
    ],
